# Trivy vulnerability waivers for the Ancora Health container images (S-78).
#
# Scanned images (see security.yml image-scan matrix):
#   - backend  — gcr.io/distroless/static-debian12:nonroot  (static Go binary,
#     ca-certificates, tzdata, /etc/passwd only; OS-package surface ~nil).
#   - frontend — gcr.io/distroless/nodejs22-debian12:nonroot (Node runtime +
#     the Next.js standalone bundle; carries a small Debian 12 userland).
#
# Policy: images must scan clean of HIGH/CRITICAL. Prefer a FIX over a waiver:
#   - Go module CVEs -> bump the module (go get) and rebuild.
#   - Base-image OS CVEs -> re-pull the distroless base once upstream rebuilds.
# Waive ONLY a finding we cannot fix ourselves (e.g. an OS package in a
# package-manager-less distroless base awaiting an upstream rebuild) AND that is
# not exploitable in this image. Every waiver MUST carry: the CVE id, the
# affected package, why it is not exploitable here, and an expiry (`exp:`) so it
# is re-evaluated rather than lingering silently. An unexplained id is a bug.
#
# Format: one CVE id per line, optionally `CVE-ID exp:YYYY-MM-DD`.
#
# --- Active waivers ---
#
# libssl3 (Debian 12) in the frontend distroless base, installed 3.0.18-1~deb12u2,
# fixed 3.0.19/3.0.20-1~deb12u2. distroless has no apt, so the patch arrives only
# when Google rebuilds nodejs22-debian12; tracked, re-pull then drop these. None
# is reachable from the Next.js standalone Node HTTP server, which does not invoke
# OpenSSL's CMS/PKCS7 or SMIME code paths. Runtime is linux/amd64 (64-bit).
#
# CVE-2026-31789 (CRITICAL): heap buffer overflow on 32-bit systems ONLY; the
# image runs on 64-bit amd64, so it is not applicable.
CVE-2026-31789 exp:2026-08-06
# CVE-2026-28387/28388/28389/28390 (HIGH): OpenSSL CMS/PKCS7 DoS (NULL deref /
# CMS parsing); the Node server never processes attacker-supplied CMS/PKCS7.
CVE-2026-28387 exp:2026-08-06
CVE-2026-28388 exp:2026-08-06
CVE-2026-28389 exp:2026-08-06
CVE-2026-28390 exp:2026-08-06
# CVE-2026-45447 (HIGH): use-after-free in OpenSSL PKCS7_verify(); PKCS7_verify
# is not called by the Next.js runtime.
CVE-2026-45447 exp:2026-08-06
